On December 22, 2020, the President signed several laws into effect. These include:

1. H.R. 1830, the "National Purple Heart Hall of Honor Commemorative Coin Act," which mandates the Department of the Treasury to mint and issue coins to commemorate the National Purple Heart Hall of Honor.

2. H.R. 3349, the "Republic of Texas Legation Memorial Act," which grants authorization to the Daughters of the Republic of Texas to establish the Republic of Texas Legation Memorial as a commemorative work in Washington, D.C.

3. S. 134, the "Combat Online Predators Act," which increases the maximum prison sentence for stalking offenses if the victim is under 18 years old.

4. S. 578, the "The ALS Disability Insurance Act of 2019," which eliminates the five-month waiting period for individuals diagnosed with amyotrophic lateral sclerosis (ALS) to receive Old Age, Survivors, and Disability Insurance benefits.

5. S. 1153, the "Stop Student Debt Relief Scams Act of 2019," which introduces penalties for unauthorized access to certain student loan information and expands the requirements for student loan exit counseling.

6. S. 3703, the "Promoting Alzheimer's Awareness to Prevent Elder Abuse Act," which mandates the Justice Department to update best practices and training materials to address victims and witnesses with Alzheimer's disease and related dementias.